{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17505939","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17505939"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:38:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:38:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2500"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2500","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2500"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.04,0.16,0.6,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2500"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"35163"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2500","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2500"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2500"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"20054"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"},{"type":"tags","id":"3026"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"12914"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2291"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2309"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42512"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"35163","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/35163"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 31 year old man is seen in the emergency department of a rural hospital after being brought in by ambulance. His girlfriend called emergency services after receiving a \u0022goodbye\u0022 text from him on her phone. According to her, he has had depression \u0022on and off\u0022 for a number of years. He attempted to hang himself in his early 20s, however this attempt was unsuccessful as the rope snapped. He is known to the local community mental health team and has an mirtazapine 30mg PO nocte dispensed on a regular basis, however he recently stopped attending mental health appointments and did not fill his most recent prescription at the pharmacy. He recently lost his job and has been drinking increased amounts of vodka since finding out.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"When assessing his risk of suicide, which one of the following features of his presentation is most concerning?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Expressed an intent to die in text message","Increased consumption of alcohol","Disengagement from mental health services and medication non-compliance","Previous suicide attempt","His gender"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer to this question is \u003Cstrong\u003Eprevious suicide attempt.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn the 10-44 age group, suicide is in the top three causes of death worldwide, with the highest rates occurring in males aged 30-59.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen assessing suicide risk, a comprehensive clinical assessment should form the main basis of assessment. Simple risk measurement tools or checklists should not be used in isolation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, the patient has suffered an acute stressor (the loss of his job), on a background of longstanding depression.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAside from these two risk factors, other risk factors present include expressing a wish to die, disengagement from mental health services, medication non-compliance, increased alcohol usage and his gender.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDespite all of these, the single biggest risk factor for a future suicide attempt is a previous suicide attempt. Any patient with a previous history of suicide or self-harm should be taken seriously and thoroughly assessed before being declared \u0022safe\u0022.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["A previous suicide attempt is the most concerning feature in the assessment of suicide risk."],"references":["Morriss R, Kapur N, Byng R. Assessing risk of suicide or self harm in adults. BMJ\u202f: British Medical Journal. 2013 Jul;347:4572\u20134572"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"20054"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2500"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"20054","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/20054"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-04-21T07:03:49+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-20T08:43:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2500"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"35163"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relatio